Description: Body fragment of North Ionian black-figured pottery closed vessel (dinos or krater?); interior reserved; exterior, brown-cream slip; part of a sphinx to right with filling ornament of rosettes; red on spots, hair, wing-covert and on alternate feathers of sphinx's wing; incision used for part of outline and details of sphinx and for field ornaments.
Excavator/field collector: Excavated by: Dr David George Hogarth
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Ashmolean Museum, Oxford. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.
Published (as an oinochoe) in CVA Oxford 2, II D, p. 81, no. 51, pl. IV.
Bibliographic references: CVA Oxford II / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum Great Britain 9 Oxford fasicule 2 (IID pl. IV, 51)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.425)
Previous owner: Currently owned by: Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford
